<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Stowe</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Cridler</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Cape Town</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-05-26"><hi rend="italic">May 26,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 81.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith
                                copy<note n="3" xml:id="d720fn3">Not printed. The proclamation,
                                after the usual preamble, quotes the rules in regard to illegal
                                enlistment and shipbuilding and the use of British ports by vessels
                                of belligerents which were published in the proclamation of
                                neutrality by Great Britain, see <ref target="#pg_865">p.
                                865</ref>.</note> of the proclamation of Her Majesty’s Government
                            regarding the neutrality to be observed during the continuance of
                            hostilities between the United States and the Kingdom of Spain.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. G. Stewe</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States Consul-General.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>